title: Did Trump’s Tulsa Rally Result in 100% Positive COVID-19 Test Rates in Oklahoma?
subtitle: An MSNBC analysis of incomplete data resulted in misunderstandings.
author: Nur Ibrahim
vclaim: U.S. President Donald Trump’s June 20, 2020, election rally in Tulsa, Oklahoma, during the coronavirus pandemic could be connected to two days of 100% positive COVID-19 tests reported in the state more than a week later.
